  <front>
   <head>The CHARMS of ANTHONY.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">YE Swains, attend; let ev'ry Nymph be near;</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Be still, ye Rivers, that the Swains may hear:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ye Winds, be calm, and brush with softer Wing;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">We mean the Charms of  to sing;</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">See all around the list'ning Shepherds throng;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O help, ye Sisters of immortal Song.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thus sung the Maids till  came by,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And  from weeding of the Rye;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Each took his Lass, and sped 'em to the Town,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To drink cool Cider at the  and</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The Damsels simper like the sparkling Beer,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And  shines till  is near.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
